# 🍽️ QR SaaS — Sprint 1: Foundation & Auth

> Turborepo monorepo · Next.js 16 · Express · PostgreSQL · JWT

---

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js ≥ 20
- pnpm ≥ 9 (`npm install -g pnpm`)
- Docker + Docker Compose

### 1 — Clone & Install

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd qr-saas

# Install all workspace deps
pnpm install
```

### 2 — Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — set JWT_SECRET, SUPER_ADMIN_PASSWORD, etc.
```

### 3 — Start Infrastructure

```bash
# Starts Postgres, Redis, and Nginx
docker compose up postgres redis -d

# Wait for health checks, then run migrations
pnpm db:migrate
```

### 4 — Start Dev Servers

```bash
# Starts both API (:3001) and Web (:3000) in parallel
pnpm dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000/register](http://localhost:3000/register)

---

## Project Structure

```
qr-saas/
├── apps/
│   ├── api/          # Express.js REST API + Socket.io
│   └── web/          # Next.js 16 frontend
└── packages/
    └── shared/       # Shared TypeScript types
```

---

## API Reference (Sprint 1)

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/v1/auth/register` | Register restaurant + owner |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/auth/login` | Login → tokens |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/auth/refresh` | Rotate refresh token |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/auth/logout` | Revoke session |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/auth/me` | Get current user |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/health` | Health check |

### Example: Register

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "email": "owner@myrestaurant.com",
    "password": "SecurePass1!",
    "firstName": "Maria",
    "lastName": "Chen",
    "restaurantName": "Chen'\''s Kitchen"
  }'
```

### Example: Login

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{ "email": "owner@myrestaurant.com", "password": "SecurePass1!" }'
```

